<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="176" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[449,1846,1031,1838]" pageId="1" pageNumber="176">
This tropicopolitan ant has a wide distribution, occurring in tropics of America, Africa, Asia, and the various groups of islands in the Pacific. 
<materialsCitation country="Guam" location="It" municipality="Fullaway" pageId="1" pageNumber="176" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-male="1">
Previously collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[798,902,1645,1687]" name="Guam" pageId="1" pageNumber="176">Guam</collectingCountry>
by 
<collectingMunicipality box="[971,1135,1645,1687]" pageId="1" pageNumber="176">Fullaway</collectingMunicipality>
in 1911. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0E4F7F497E655A2EB493FB83105C717A:833998847E655A2EB070F9E9131770C3" box="[1314,1344,1645,1687]" country="Guam" municipality="Fullaway" name="It" pageId="1" pageNumber="176">It</location>
is a large black species with long mandibles. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0E4F7F497E655A2EB493FB83105C717A:833998847E655A2EB7AEF9241512709E" box="[764,837,1696,1738]" country="Guam" municipality="Fullaway" name="One" pageId="1" pageNumber="176">One</location>
winged 
<specimenCount box="[1004,1087,1696,1738]" pageId="1" pageNumber="176" type="male">male</specimenCount>
was collected in house, but we collected most of the others among leaves and trash on the ground in the forest areas. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0E4F7F497E655A2EB493FB83105C717A:833998847E655A2EB496F8821449717A" box="[452,542,1798,1838]" country="Guam" municipality="Fullaway" name="Once" pageId="1" pageNumber="176">Once</location>
a colony was found at the base of a rotten banana stem
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
